    <text type="note" xml:lang="ru" xml:id="letter-09089"> 
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when-custom="1788-10-07">1788 г. Октября 7.</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Дайте о сем приказании знать <persName ref="people.xml#sut01">Сутерланду</persName>, чтоб <rs ref="people.xml#sut01">он</rs> видел, что я, кой час до меня доходит, умею взять меры для исправнаго платежа, чрез что возстановила и сохраняю кредит двадцать седьмой год. 
                <note type="editorial">
                    According to A.V. Khrapovitskii's diary, Catherine writes about her order to the <persName ref="people.xml#vya01">Procurator General Aleksandr Alekseevich Viazemskii</persName> to pay to <persName ref="people.xml#sut01">baron Sutherland</persName> 229,473 rubles (
                    <bibl>
                        <title ref="works.xml#dnevni01">Dnevnik A.V. Khrapovitskogo 1782-1793</title>
                        , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 168.</biblScope>
                    </bibl>
                    ).
                    It might be referring to the fact that <persName ref="people.xml#sut01">Sutherland</persName> was lending money to many of the magnates near to Catherine, among them <persName ref="people.xml#pot01">G.A. Potemkin</persName>, <persName ref="people.xml#bez01">A.A. Bezborodko</persName>, <persName ref="people.xml#ost05">I.A. Ostermann</persName>, <persName ref="people.xml#vya01">A.A. Viazemskii</persName>, and even <persName ref="people.xml#pau01">Grand Duke Pavel Petrovich</persName>. Viazemskii and Bezborodko cleared their debts and the others promised to do so later (
                    <bibl>
                        <title ref="works.xml#suther01">The Sutherland Affair and Its Aftermath</title>
                        , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 259.</biblScope>;
                        <title ref="works.xml#vndolg01">Vneshnii dolg Rossiiskoi imperii v 1775-1787</title>
                        , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 108.</biblScope>
                    </bibl>
                    ).
                </note>
            </p>
        </body>
